     <div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10 col-lg-offset-2 col-lg-8 body-text">
      <section aria-label="Summary">
       <h2 class="sr-only">
        Summary
       </h2>
       <!-- begin code region 'pod_3530325' -->
       <div class=" wv-code-region-pod_3530325">
        <p>
         <span class="headline">
          The UC Berkeley Department of Film &amp; Media
         </span>
         offers innovative, interdisciplinary programs leading to a B.A. in Film and a Ph.D. in Film &amp; Media. It also provides curricular support for the Designated Emphasis in Film Studies for doctoral students in other departments. The Department teaches students to think historically, theoretically, and analytically about film and media within the broad context of humanistic studies. Students and faculty engage with all forms of moving-image culture, including film, still photography, television, and digital media. The Department also offers courses in screenwriting, curating, and digital video production.
        </p>
       </div>
       <!-- end code region pod_3530325 -->
      </section>
